# Path-level redirects (Cloudflare Pages).
# Format:  /old-path   /new-path   301
# Port any redirects currently configured in Webflow here at cutover.
#
# NOTE: apex -> www is NOT handled here. Pages _redirects matches on path,
# not hostname, so the apex redirect is a Redirect Rule in the Cloudflare
# dashboard instead — see README ("Deploy to Cloudflare Pages").
# Legacy Webflow pages (old copy, superseded by the new homepage + use-cases).
/products                 /                                    301
/products/                /                                    301
/product                  /                                    301
/account-based-sales      /use-cases/account-based-outreach    301
/account-based-sales/     /use-cases/account-based-outreach    301

# Old customer-story slug -> current slug.
/customerstories/workspace   /customerstories/workspace365     301

# Conventional /sitemap.xml -> the generated sitemap index.
/sitemap.xml   /sitemap-index.xml   301
